# Site-wide component library (required)

This project has **one component library for the entire site** — landing, case study, about, resume, and password gate all share the same primitives.

**Always use existing components.** Do not create page-specific buttons, cards, or duplicate markup unless the user explicitly asks for a new component.

## Site-wide primitives (use everywhere)

These are defined once in Figma and once in code. **Same `Button` on home, case study, resume, and everywhere else.**

| Component | Import | Used on |
|-----------|--------|---------|
| `Button` | `@/components/ui/button` | All pages |
| `Card` | `@/components/ui/card` | Home project links, case study sections, resume, etc. |
| `SiteHeader` | `@/components/SiteHeader` | All pages (via `SiteLayout`) |
| `SiteContainer` | `@/components/SiteContainer` | All pages |

## Before building any UI

1. Check `design-reference/COMPONENTS.md` — site-wide catalog
2. Check `src/components/ui/` for primitives
3. Check `src/components/` for site shell
4. Compose pages from shared primitives — never fork a "case study button" or "home card"

## Folder structure

| Folder | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `src/components/ui/` | **Site-wide primitives** from Figma (Button, Card, …) |
| `src/components/` | **Site shell** shared by all pages |
| `src/components/portfolio/` | **Composed blocks** that *use* `Card`/`Button` — not alternate primitives |
| `src/pages/` | Thin page wrappers only |

## Rules

- Case study sections → `Card` + tokens, not custom `<article>` card markup
- Project links on home → `Card`, same as elsewhere
- Need a button anywhere → `Button` from `ui/button`, never `<button className="...">` with one-off styles
- New Figma component → implement once in `ui/` or `components/`, register in `COMPONENTS.md`, use site-wide

## Do NOT

- Create `CaseStudyButton`, `HomeCard`, or page-scoped variants of shared components
- Put primitives under `portfolio/` — that folder composes primitives, it does not replace them
- Add ShadCN components without user asking

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — case study-only card markup
<article className="rounded-2xl bg-card p-6 shadow-elevation-1">...</article>

// ❌ BAD — one-off button on one page
<button className="rounded-lg bg-primary px-4 py-2">Next</button>

// ✅ GOOD — same Card and Button as the rest of the site
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Card, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card"
```

## Page / case study handoffs

When the user shares a page or case study frame built from Figma components:

1. Read `design-reference/PAGE-HANDOFF.md` if they filled it in
2. Match **Figma instance names** to `COMPONENTS.md` (Figma `Button` → code `Button`, same variants)
3. Compose the page from catalog components only — no raw divs that duplicate Button/Card
4. Unrecognized Figma component → ask before creating anything new
